<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=417&amp;p=2235#p2235"><![CDATA[
its not yet Built in, but the Creator of Classic Shell, IVO, has given us this Manual method for adding &quot;Pin to Classic Start Menu&quot; Right-Click Menu Item:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=5&amp;t=61">http://classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=5&amp;t=61</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Its very easy, here's the quick &amp; dirty version:<br /><br />1. Download <strong><a href="http://classicshell.net/forum/download/file.php?id=203" class="postlink">PinToCSM.zip</a></strong> and <strong><a href="http://www.optimumx.com/downloads.html#ShellExecute" class="postlink">ShellExecute.exe</a></strong><br /><br />2. Unzip PinToCSM to Extract &quot;makelink.exe&quot; &amp; a .Reg File<br /><br />3. Drag ShellExecute.exe &amp; makelink.exe to C:\Windows, Click Yes to any Prompts<br /><br />4. Double-Click the .Reg file, and Click Yes to any Prompts<br /><br />5. Select as many files as you want to pin, right-click, select &quot;Pin to Classic Start Menu&quot;, and watch the magic happen<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=359">Tenzen</a> — Mon Mar 25, 2013 5:05 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
