<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=417&amp;p=2157#p2157"><![CDATA[
This seems to be one of the only things left that Classic Shell can't replicate from the real start menu: On Windows Vista and 7, when you go to all programs or search for something, it gets shown in the left pane instead of a popout menu. Of course, having this be optional would be the  best for people who still want a popout menu.<br /><br />The only other thing missing, that I can think of is not having a &quot;Pin to start button&quot; option on Windows 8 when you right click on an executable or a shortcut.<br /><br />Thanks for reading this and creating such a useful program.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=488">webulator70</a> — Fri Mar 22, 2013 12:53 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
